README

This directory contains the source code for the classic hello-world
program written in several programming languages, including C++, C,
Fortran, and Java.

    hello.c
        The source code for the hello-world program written in C.
    hello.cpp
        The source code for the hello-world program written in C++.
    hello.f
        The source code for the hello-world program written in Fortran.
    hello.java
        The source code for the hello-world program written in Java.

The code in this directory can be built using CMake with the CMakeLists
file provided.

To run the Java program after building (on a Linux-based system), use a
command like:

    java -cp hello_java.jar hello

